A GNUstep preference pane and daemon for global keyboard shortcuts on FreeBSD systems.

This package provides:
- A GNUstep preference pane for configuring global keyboard shortcuts
- A daemon (globalshortcutsd) that monitors and executes keyboard shortcuts
- Integration with X11 for system-wide keyboard event handling

Features:
- Configure custom keyboard shortcuts for launching applications
- System-wide hotkey monitoring using X11
- User-friendly graphical configuration interface
- Lightweight daemon with minimal resource usage

The daemon reads configuration from ~/.globalshortcutsrc and supports
common shortcut formats like "ctrl+shift+t=xterm".
